Added brief message.
Updated XML Aeroscope Display file to reflect most recent changes.
Commented out old stuff regarding text views.

Updated Aeroscope commands, both the array.xml and the command array found in Constants.
Also created new method in Device called StopAndCancel.
Implemented Device power state in AeroscopeDevice.java. Added an enum inside of Aeroscope constants for various device power levels.
Defined critical error codes.
Updated build.grade for App module.
Redid stuff in Aeroscope constants, commented out some vestigial commands that Aeroscope currently is not using.
Changed some imports, renamed COMMAND_ARRAY to USER_COMMAND_ARRAY.
Redid some of the Aeroscope Commands, changed the order to match the Spreadsheet.
Updated gradle version.
Streamlined the User commands array to match what we have in Aeroscope Constants.
Random misc changes, unimportant.
Removed deprecated call.
Max aeroscopes = 1.
Added calling context inside of mainactivity.
Jack commit April 10.
New branch JackTestBranch.
Added a new class (AeroscopePreferences) and added a line to doOnConnected inside of AeroscopeDisplay.java.
Added PNG images for various battery states.
Re-added .PNG images with correct capitalization & spelling.

Replaced text battery with graphic.
I BELIEVE this causes app crash.
Reverted graphing library to 3.0.1.
Initial Commit for New Jack Branch
First test of ConnectionSharingAdapter.
First commit of UIAdditions
Added two new graphics for connected and disconnected. Implemented code.
Aeroscope Display minor additions.
bogus misc.xml update
Got the trigger dialogue pop-up working semi-correctly, gives the user various trigger options. However, seems to have error where all modes are disabled upon hitting OK.
Wahoo, now the trigger dialog works correctly, remembers user selections inbetween presses of the Trigger button. Seems to be running smoothly.
AC/DC Coupling works! Got dat switch and everything.
Aeroscope Display - added new button to start/stop the probe.
Fixed a few bugs that might fix it.
Updated start/stop button logic, fixed old comments.
Changed text on start/stop button. XML formatting change to AC/DC switch.
Potential fix for AeroscopeArrayAdapter in the MainActivity class that aims to clear the found devices directly after the user selects one.
Moved potential fix down two lines.
Potential fix #2. Added the Aeroscope array adapter declaration to be outside of the broadcast receiver inner class.
Fixed potential nullptr issue.
Changed the Aeroscope command spinner, removed the start/stop commands from it. Updated various other code to reflect changes.
Updated command spinner with initial dummy command so that the Stop/Get single frame isn't automatically executed upon intialization.

Hopefully solved the recursive call issue related to resetting the Command Spinner to its default, no-op position after executing a real command.
In the command processing switch, if the command just executed was not the dummy, then we schedule the dummy command for a future time.
Removed all of the dead comments, I believe.
Merged Version4Alex with FixedCommandsTry4, added small comment at the end to allow for a commit.
